<!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD XHTML 1.0 Strict//EN" "http://www.w3.org/TR/xhtml1/DTD/xhtml1-strict.dtd">
<!-- We need a doctype to allow us to use special characters like &nbsp; 
	 We use a "strict" DTD to make IE follow the alignment rules. -->
	 
<html xmlns:t="http://tapestry.apache.org/schema/tapestry_5_3.xsd">
<head>
	<link rel="stylesheet" type="text/css" href="${context:css/examples/examples.css}"/>
	<style type="text/css">
		.eg				{ background: #eee; }
		.eg table		{ border-collapse: collapse; width: 40%; font-size: 13px; }
		.eg table th	{ padding: 2px 5px; text-align: right; width: 35%; color: #999; }
		.eg table td	{ padding: 2px 5px; text-align: left; }
	</style>
</head>
<body>
	<h1>Total Control Output</h1>
	
	This page demonstrates how to display an object without using BeanDisplay.  On the minus side, it takes more lines of 
	template code.  On the plus side, you have total control of the	content, layout and style.

	<div class="eg">
		<table>
			<tr>
				<th>Id:</th>
				<td>${person.id}</td>
			</tr>
			<tr>
				<th>Version:</th>
				<td>${person.version}</td>
			</tr>
			<tr>
				<th>Name:</th>
				<td>${person.lastName}, ${person.firstName}</td>
			</tr>
			<tr>
				<th>Region:</th>
				<td>${personRegion}</td>
			</tr>
			<tr>
				<th>Start Date:</th>
				<td><t:output t:value="person.startDate" format="startDateFormat"/></td>
			</tr>
		</table>
	</div>
	
	Person is an EJB3 Entity Bean, PersonFinderService is an EJB3 Stateless Session Bean.<br/><br/>
	
	References: 
	<a href="http://tapestry.apache.org/5.3.6/apidocs/org/apache/tapestry5/corelib/components/Output.html">Output component</a>.<br/><br/>	
	
	<t:pagelink t:page="Index" href="#">Home</t:pagelink><br/><br/>
	
	The source for PersonFinderService, @EJB handling, etc. is shown in the @EJB example.<br/><br/>
	
